    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.10.6" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">6</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">ALLEN TUPPER TRUE
                        <lb/>
                    DENVER, COLORADO</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Mar. 12. 1923</dateline>
                
                    <salute>My Dear Mr. Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>It is almost impossible to set a date for a visit to you because the capitol decoration commission keeps postponing the time for placing my panels in the <unclear>Ms.</unclear> capitol. Also I am still in the clutches of the "flue<sic>flu</sic>" and altho<sic>although</sic> trying to work, am not at all sure of myself. This is the first day for a week that I have been at the studio.</p>
                
                <p>So please let me call you up from Jeff. City or write to you from there &#8212; and take a chance on connecting. I shall have to be in Jefferson City for a week or ten days and we ought to be able to manage it in that time. I am not going <unclear/> on you however for all I'm fond of Jersey cream.</p> 
                
                <p>Many thanks for autographing my copy of Hugh Glass. I value it more highly than ever now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Allen T. True</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
